    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      RGN_AND
      The new clipping region includes the intersection (overlapping areas) of the current clipping region and the current path (or new region).(${t_e372ade806034931b2f0f9dc59ee1955})
      RGN_COMPLEMENT
      This is the opposite of RGN_DIFF, and only made-up for compatibility with EMF+(${t_97798cfa993847eea668e1e5ecb39d4d})
      RGN_COPY
      The new clipping region is the current path (or the new region).(${t_235fb680e5c44711ac1dddb48a3612af})
      RGN_DIFF
      The new clipping region includes the areas of the current clipping region with those of the current path (or new region) excluded.(${t_5d48195b6d25406e91fc36b9b49f0f3b})
      RGN_OR
      The new clipping region includes the union (combined areas) of the current clipping region and the current path (or new region).(${t_69c8a8c3bab24ba395f76dc69184c6ab})
      RGN_XOR
      The new clipping region includes the union of the current clipping region and the current path (or new region) but without the overlapping areas(${t_c1f737519e4a49a1ad2ccc7588de55ce})
